



/// How to change the app name and icon ?


// For Android 

- Android app name -> android:label =>> android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml

- Android app icon -> android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"> 
    from -> android/app/src/main/res/mipmap-mdpi/ic_launcher.png && all other sizes
    we can use external extinction to help us


// For IOS

- IOS app name -> ios/Runner/Info.plist -> search for -> 
    <key>CFBundleName</key>
	<string>complete_dev_guide</string>
    
    change <string>complete_dev_guide</string> to the name you want , in our ex <string>Flutter Guide</string> 


// create assets folder in the app folders 

- add a package named flutter_launcher_icons: "last version"
link: https://pub.dev/packages/flutter_launcher_icons/install
 * add in the terminal -> flutter pub add flutter_launcher_icons

 follow the guid 
 https://pub.dev/packages/flutter_launcher_icons#book-guide

- choose "download" the logo you want and added it to pubspec.yaml file